tip.text: Kuey Chap, O-Jian, simple Char Kuay Teow, Lobak, and there is a small Mua Chi at a dark corner that sells really good Mua Chi!!
Can't get this consistency of Asam Laksa KL. Usually those in KL are too watery. Pasar Air Itam Asam Laksa had a thick flavorful broth with the right amount of spiciness that keeps you wanting more

formattedAddress: LG 115, Food Street, One Utama Shopping Center
location.address: LG 115, Food Street, One Utama Shopping Center

tip.text: Pork ribs were good but not as good compared to the original one in Bali. Rm26 Roast pork salad was appetizing but IMO too pricey for this plate of salad

Homely feel, loved the "build your own meal" option with their meatballs. Must try the mushroom balls, better than the chicken and beef balls. I chose the mixed balls paired with pasta, pesto and nuts
Fresh slices of cold cuts. Authentic Italian food & Great service as always!

formattedAddress: Lot G12, F101 & S101, 1 Utama Shopping Centre (Lebuh Bandar Utama)
location.address: Lot G12, F101 & S101, 1 Utama Shopping Centre

tip.text: Be ready for what seems like a never ending steps. Haha. But no worries it is doable. There are many small routes so keep a compass and the Bukit Gasing map (below) in handy.
Price is on the higher side but the Nachos and Sloppy fries is good for sharing.

formattedAddress: K-G-2A Palm Square, Jaya One Shopping Centre
location.address: K-G-2A Palm Square, Jaya One Shopping Centre

tip.text: I would say, Don't expect too much. Breakfast spread was better than the dinner.
Fresh seafood! Their Lobster is huge! Must try the fried squid.
Different style if BKT. Food come in individual bowls, soup is slightly diluted (different from the KL type), food was good!

venue.name: Yu Kee Bak Kut Teh (佑記肉骨茶)

tip.text: Clear water and we swam with the fishes! Less people compared to Pulau Manukan. Be sure to try the Coral Flyer!

formattedAddress: Tunku Abdul Rahman National Park (3-8KM offshore Kota Kinabalu City)

tip.text: Touristy and packed but if you are willing to drive 2 1/2 hours from KK town to get fresh from the farm gelato, yogurt and milk, then yes do it!!
I order the normal mixed beef noodles. The meat was fresh and the broth was very appetizing. Loads of beef slices in there! 👍👍👍

venue.name: Kah Hiong Ngiu Chap 家乡牛什

formattedAddress: Kolam Centre Phase 2 (Lrg Cina, Off Jln Lintas)

tip.text: The ambiance here is comfy and quaintly decorated. However i find that the food are overpriced for the quality and portion. Pictured is the Williams Cottage Cheese Waffle for Rm25.90.
The property was well kept, clean and fully equipped. Hisham was a good host in ensuring that the campers will have a good time there

formattedAddress: Batu 7, Kampung Asli Sungai Cincin, Chenderiang
location.address: Batu 7, Kampung Asli Sungai Cincin, Chenderiang

tip.text: I love their Lemon Meringue tart and softshell crab pasta. Pan Mee Impasta (pictured) was different but too salty for my liking
Definitely better than the other cheese tart brands. The filling was soft like soufflé, cream cheese wasn't too heavy or thick. Crust was baked to perfection.
Their portions are HUGE!! My usual order is the dry pho with lemongrass chicken and spring roll. Their beef soup is also good!

formattedAddress: 1 Utama Shopping Centre, Lot S 312, 2nd Floor (Lebuh Bandar Utama, Bandar Utama)
location.address: 1 Utama Shopping Centre, Lot S 312, 2nd Floor

tip.text: Ordered the Pitaya bowl & Vatte (almond mylk + double shot espresso). The smoothie was thick, granola was toasted and crunchy. Vatte had an extra nutty taste cause of the almond mylk!

location.neighborhood: Taman Tun Doktor Ismail, Kuala Lumpur, Kuala Lumpur

tip.text: Come here for a selection of healthy choices, including gluten free products. Order from the breakfast set for refillable coffee/tea up till 11am.

At Rm15.50 without GST, come here for fluffly french toast using Hailam bread. Choose between a selection of flavours of Kaya/Chocolate/Strawberry/Peanut Butter for the stuffing. Prices are reasonable
New York Bagel Platter (Rm120) for 2 but actually can feed a party of 4 with extra! Comes with 3 types of cream cheese spread. This platter is only available on weekends. Bagels are refillable.
Portion is reasonably big (food to fist comparison in pic) and food quality is good for the price. They just started operations in January 2017 so the service was SUPER SLOW.
Great place for healthy food options. Industrial interior, plenty of seats and plug points and fast wifi! Nice place to chill and work
Their big breakfast is really BIG and only at RM15. Pizza seems to be popular here.

tip.text: Salade Japonaise was just ok.. nothing special.
Recommend the Tuna Tartae, Salmon Mentai pasta, Avocado Chicken, Nara Donburi (though it can get a little too much). Tried the Chicken Waffle, it's good but i personally prefer the classic waffle  😁
Superbowl salad is a protein packed salad bowl which contains prawns, beef, chicken, sausage with loads of veges including avocado.
Highly recommend the coconut soup! Can't get that kinda good stuff in Malaysia. Thai basil chicken had a strong earthy taste not to my liking.

tip.text: Tried a couple of the weekly specials (pic shows Pork Lasagna) & i must say the Spaghetti Vongole is one of the best clam pasta i've tasted. For the quality, the price is worth it.

formattedAddress: Lot G12, F101 & S101, 1 Utama Shopping Centre (Lebuh Bandar Utama)
location.address: Lot G12, F101 & S101, 1 Utama Shopping Centre

tip.text: Most people raved about the pavlova (tried that too and i understand why) but the Baked cookie in a pan deserves a mention too. It's the real deal. Gooey, crumbly & rich in chocolatey goodness
Tried Starters & Mains-Flat Bread, fresh bread, appetizing yogurt chives dipping; Grilled Duck Breast, Spring Chicken, both juicy & tender; Duck Fat Potatoes, deliciously light texture. Quality 👍🏻
Tom Yum (red) soup with bee hoon! Somehow feel that the tom yum soup here is much more spicier compared to the other outlets. They allowed my request to change my bee hoon to glass noodles too (yay!)
V3 is my go to. If you prefer the vermicelli spring roll, you can request to change. I've been here a few times and I have a theory that at night the portion is bigger compared to lunch time. LOL
Tried the pork chop with black pepper sauce. It was just ok for me, perhaps i was expecting more, not as good as what my friends were raving about.
Did take away for Sashimi & Ootoro. Really fresh. It was a full house at the restaurant on a public holiday, we were advised to make reservation 1-2 days prior for weekend/holidays

location.neighborhood: Mont Kiara, Kuala Lumpur, Kuala Lumpur

tip.text: Sundubu Jigae is the bomb here. The tofus are damn huge. Tried the Bibimbap, very not worth the price and side dishes are only refillable once.
Gyoza is not bad but personally not a fan of their ramen. My friend and i felt that the broth was very salty. I've had better ones, this for the portion and ingredients, is not worth the price.

tip.text: Quite an underrated place. Quiet environment. They have lunch sets as well. Portions are big.
Besides the coffee, food here is not bad. Ordered the Pesto Pasta and it's flavour was really pure. Big portion too.

tip.text: Thai Milk Tea is addictive, Tried the Basil Pork Rice, Roasted Pork Neck and Grilled Pork Skewers. Porky goodness!
Foodwise, Tom Yum pasta with Pandan Chicken is good (spicy and flavourful) though the Tom Yum sauce tastes more like Chilli Crab
The croissants are fantastic! Even just the basic ones. The pastry is light, flaky and gives the 'crunch' when you run your knife through it. I highly recommend their Matcha Latte, deliciously thick!

venue.name: Basilica of Santa Croce (Basilica di Santa Croce)

tip.text: A cosy joint to have healthy eats. Tuna tartar was worth the try. They gave a generous portion of raw tuna chunks which were very fresh too! I shall be back for a taste of a different dish 👍🏻
Pork noodles with 2 eggs. Lots of meat and full of flavor at every spoon.
Brought guests there after a rainy night and they liked it. 360 degrees scenic view and the air was cooling and windy. Romantic for dates. ;)
Generally the food here is good; we usually order the chicken, fishballs, meatballs, taugeh with Hor Fun. Definitely much better than the commercialized ones around in Ipoh.

venue.name: Restoran Kah Seng Ipoh Tauge Ayam Kuetiau

tip.text: The Banana Pancake is fluffy and slightly crisp on the surface. Soft on the inside and they gave a generous amount of maple syrup. A heavenly start to a great morning!

location.city: เมืองเชียงใหม่

tip.text: Their breakfast is good! Bread is fresh and nicely crisp. Eggs are large and packed with ingredients. Banana pancake is truly love!

formattedAddress: เมืองเชียงใหม่
location.city: เมืองเชียงใหม่

tip.text: Tried 4 cakes from here,Green Tea Mille Crepe still tops as my favorite so far!

Tried their Red Velvet Cake which they heat it up before serving and you get the chocolate oozing out. The cake is not sweet at all. Everything from the cream cheese to the chocolate drizzle goes well
It's so hard to get good salted caramel cake around here but their Salted Cookie Chocolate.. Awesome! Generous amount of chocolate with cookie bits and the salted caramel has the right consistency.
Chicken is different in the sense that it is fragrant and flavorful with spices. And they make the sunny side up perfectly! 😍
Quaint and cosy store. Portion was just nice for a small eater like me. The pork cutlet was fried but not oily. Loved the simplicity of the ambience and food!

tip.text: One of the best pork ribs I've tried! Tender, falls off easily, smokey and glazed with the right amount and taste. Their chicken soup was clear and light with added vegetables just the way i like it.
Very windy but food very slow.
My first visit here and i ordered the Tamarind Prawn Angel Hair Pasta. It was an interesting flavour, if you have a thing for sour food then you should try this. It has a very tangy taste!
